# Frontend Full Redesign Plan

## Requirements Summary

Full visual redesign and component refactor of the Online Judge frontend using a multi-source design system (Linear base + Notion/Supabase/Vercel/Sentry/ClickHouse/PostHog/Cursor/Stripe overlays). shadcn/ui + Radix for component primitives. Dark-first with light toggle. Chrome 109 minimum. Core coding flow prioritized.

## Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| Scope | Full redesign + refactor | User chose comprehensive overhaul of all 44 pages |
| Theme | Dark-first, light toggle available | Developer-heavy user base; matches Linear/Supabase aesthetic |
| Priority | Core coding flow first | 80%+ of user time is in ProblemSet/ProblemDetail/IDE/Submission |
| Components | shadcn/ui + Radix UI | Headless primitives, fully customizable, Chrome 109 compatible |
| Browser min | Chrome 109 | Last Chrome on Windows 7 (school environment constraint) |
| Design system | Linear base + scene overlays | Per the awesome-design-md recommendations discussion |

## Browser Compatibility

- **Target**: Chrome 109+ (Vite `build.target: ['chrome109']`)
- **Constraints**: No native CSS nesting, no View Transitions, no `popover`, no `color-mix()`, no scroll-driven animations
- **Mitigation**: Tailwind compiles all CSS; Vite transpiles JS; Radix UI provides fallbacks for all interactive patterns

## Design Token Architecture

### Base Layer — Linear (all pages)
- Background: `#08090a` (dark), `#f7f8f8` (light)
- Text hierarchy: `#f7f8f8` → `#d0d6e0` → `#8a8f98` → `#62666d`
- Border: `rgba(255,255,255,0.05~0.08)` (dark)
- Brand accent: `#5e6ad2` / `#7170ff`
- Font: Inter Variable (display/body), Berkeley Mono (code)
- Radius: `4px` (default), `6px` (cards), `9999px` (pills)

### Scene Overlays
| Scene | Source | Key Tokens |
|-------|--------|------------|
| Problem reading | Notion | Warm whites `#f6f5f4`, thin borders, soft shadows |
| Code editor/IDE | Supabase | `#3ecf8e` green accent, `#242424` border depth |
| Submissions/judging | Sentry | `#c2ef4e` green, `#fa7faa` pink, glass panels |
| Rankings/data | Vercel | Shadow-as-border, Geist compressed numbers |
| Contests live | ClickHouse | `#faff69` on black, Inter 900, extreme contrast |
| User profile | PostHog | Warm sage/olive, `#fdfdf8` parchment bg |
| Problem detail | Cursor | 3-font system (display + serif + mono) |

### Unified Status Colors
| Status | Color | Source |
|--------|-------|--------|
| Accepted | `#3ecf8e` | Supabase |
| Wrong Answer | `#cf2d56` | Cursor |
| Pending/Running | `#0a72ef` | Vercel |
| Time Limit | `#ffb287` | Sentry |
| Runtime Error | `#fa7faa` | Sentry |
| Easy | `#10b981` | Linear |
| Medium | `#F7A501` | PostHog |
| Hard | `#ff5b4f` | Vercel |

## Implementation Phases

### Phase 0: Foundation (setup, 1 step)
1. **Install shadcn/ui + configure Tailwind v4 with new design tokens**
   - Files: `tailwind.config.js`, `package.json`, `frontend/src/lib/utils.ts`, `frontend/src/styles/globals.css`
   - Add `@radix-ui/react-*` primitives via shadcn CLI
   - Set Vite `build.target: ['chrome109']`
   - Create `frontend/src/lib/design-tokens.ts` with all token values
   - Verify: `npm run build` succeeds, design tokens compile

### Phase 1: Core Component Library (building blocks)
Build the shadcn/ui component set styled with Linear + scene tokens:

1. **Layout primitives**: Container, Sidebar, Header, MobileNav
   - Refs: `frontend/src/layouts/MainLayout.tsx`, `frontend/src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx`, `frontend/src/components/layout/Header.tsx`, `frontend/src/components/layout/MobileNav.tsx`
