## Acceptance Criteria

1. All 44 pages render correctly in Chrome 109 on Windows 7
2. Dark mode is default; light mode toggle works without visual artifacts
3. Design tokens are the single source of truth (no hardcoded colors in pages)
4. Core coding flow (ProblemSet → ProblemDetail → IDE → Submission) is visually consistent and feels cohesive
5. `npm run build` succeeds with 0 errors
6. `npx tsc --noEmit` passes
7. Lighthouse Performance > 85, Accessibility > 90
8. All existing functionality preserved (routes, auth, API calls, websockets)
9. No JavaScript features beyond Chrome 109 support are used in production build
10. shadcn/ui components are installed via CLI, not hand-written

## Risks and Mitigations

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|------------|
| Chrome 109 incompatibility in a dependency | HIGH | Pin Vite target; test in Chrome 109 emulator; check Radix UI browser support matrix |
| Design token inconsistency across 44 pages | MEDIUM | Single `design-tokens.ts` file; Tailwind theme extends from tokens; CI check for hardcoded colors |
| Large CSS bundle from 9 design systems | MEDIUM | Only import tokens, not full stylesheets; Tailwind tree-shakes unused classes |
| Breaking existing functionality during refactor | HIGH | Phase by page; keep existing routes/API contracts; test each phase before next |
| Monaco Editor theme conflict with new tokens | LOW | Custom Monaco theme using design token values |
| Context window too small for 44-page rewrite | HIGH | Execute phase by phase using ralph; each phase is independent |

## Verification Steps

Per phase:
1. `npx tsc --noEmit` — type safety
2. `npm run build` — production build succeeds
3. Visual smoke test in Chrome 109 (or closest available)
4. `cargo test --lib` — backend unaffected
5. Existing test files (`__tests__/`) still pass

Final:
- Cross-browser check: Chrome 109, Chrome latest, Firefox latest
- Lighthouse audit on all phase-2 pages
- Full regression of auth, submission, and admin flows
